{%- comment -%}
  LOOQ ∞ watermark — the actual brand-supplied peanut/infinity mark
  (assets/looq-infinity-mark.png — black silhouette, 453×249).

  Uses CSS mask-image so the icon shape is "cut out" from the
  background-color. The parent's `color` property drives the visible
  tint via `background-color: currentColor`. That keeps the one-snippet
  / per-page-tint pattern working with no JS or filter chains.
{%- endcomment -%}
<span class="looq-infinity" style="--looq-infinity-mark: url('{{ 'looq-infinity-mark.png' | asset_url }}');" aria-hidden="true"></span>

{% stylesheet %}
.looq-infinity {
  display: block;
  width: 100%; height: 100%;
  background-color: currentColor;
  -webkit-mask: var(--looq-infinity-mark) no-repeat center / contain;
          mask: var(--looq-infinity-mark) no-repeat center / contain;
  pointer-events: none; user-select: none;
}
{% endstylesheet %}
